Docs.summary: Returns whether the AP requires frame protection for ranging measurement.

remarks.para: Returns whether the AP requires frame protection for ranging measurement.

Ranging frame protection in IEEE 802.11az, also known as URNM-MFPR (Unassociated Range Negotiation and Measurement Management Frame Protection Required), is a security policy that dictates whether ranging frames are required to be protected even without a formal association between the Initiating STA (ISTA) and Responding STA (RSTA)
Portions of this page are modifications based on work created and shared by the Android Open Source Project and used according to terms described in the Creative Commons 2.5 Attribution License.

Docs.summary: Returns whether the AP supports secure HE-LTF for ranging measurement.

remarks.para: Returns whether the AP supports secure HE-LTF for ranging measurement.

Secure HE-LTF (High Efficiency Long Training Field), is a security enhancement for the HE PHY (High Efficiency Physical Layer) that aims to protect ranging measurements by using randomized HE-LTF sequences. This prevents attackers from exploiting predictable HE-LTF patterns. IEEE 802.11az adds secure HE-LTF support in Extended RSN capabilities.
Portions of this page are modifications based on work created and shared by the Android Open Source Project and used according to terms described in the Creative Commons 2.5 Attribution License.
